<header class="page-header">
  <p class="eyebrow">Founded 2024 · St Tropez &amp; London</p>
  <h1>Our Story</h1>
  <div class="header-divider"></div>
</header>

<div class="story-hero"></div>

<section class="chapter">
  <div class="chapter-img" style="background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1530653333484-8a01a3b07cca?w=1200&amp;q=80');"></div>
  <div class="chapter-text">
    <p class="ch-eyebrow">The Beginning</p>
    <h2>Born from the Mediterranean light.</h2>
    <p>Tidal began on a quiet morning in St Tropez, where the colour of the sea seemed to demand something simpler, more considered. We were tired of swimwear that looked the same under every shoreline, that fell apart by the end of summer, that was made in places we couldn&rsquo;t name.</p>
    <p>So we started with a single idea: a swimsuit you would want to wear for a decade. Cut beautifully. Sewn in the United Kingdom. Made from materials we could trace from spool to seam.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="chapter reverse">
  <div class="chapter-img" style="background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1583846783214-7229a91b20ed?w=1200&amp;q=80');"></div>
  <div class="chapter-text">
    <p class="ch-eyebrow">The Craft</p>
    <h2>Slow making, by hand.</h2>
    <p>Every Tidal piece is cut and sewn in a small studio outside London by a team of seven. We work in capsule collections rather than seasons, releasing only what we believe in and producing only what is ordered.</p>
    <p>Our recycled Italian fabric is woven from regenerated ocean plastics &mdash; soft, sculpting, and engineered to hold its shape past a hundred swims. Nothing is rushed. Nothing is wasted.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="quote-band">
  <blockquote>&ldquo;We wanted to make the kind of swimwear our mothers would have kept &mdash; the kind you fold carefully at the end of summer and reach for again the next.&rdquo;</blockquote>
  <cite>&mdash; Eloise &amp; Marina, Founders</cite>
</section>

<section class="chapter">
  <div class="chapter-img" style="background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1559494007-9f5847c49d94?w=1200&amp;q=80');"></div>
  <div class="chapter-text">
    <p class="ch-eyebrow">The Promise</p>
    <h2>Quietly built to last.</h2>
    <p>We choose to be small. We choose to make less. We choose suppliers we have visited, dyes that meet OEKO-TEX standards, and packaging that returns to the earth.</p>
    <p>None of this is loud, and that is the point. A Tidal piece should sit in your suitcase year after year &mdash; familiar, soft, and unmistakably yours.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="values">
  <h2>What we stand for</h2>
  <p class="subtitle">Three principles that shape every decision we make &mdash; from the studio to your wardrobe.</p>
  <div class="value-grid">
    <div class="value-item">
      <span class="value-num">I.</span>
      <h3>Considered design</h3>
      <p>Cuts that flatter every body. Colours pulled from the coast. Pieces designed to outlast trends, not chase them.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="value-item">
      <span class="value-num">II.</span>
      <h3>Honest materials</h3>
      <p>Recycled Italian fabric. OEKO-TEX certified dyes. Fully traceable from fibre to finish &mdash; no shortcuts, no greenwashing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="value-item">
      <span class="value-num">III.</span>
      <h3>Made in the UK</h3>
      <p>Sewn by a small team outside London who are paid fairly and know every piece by name.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cta">
  <h2>Discover the collection</h2>
  <p>Capsule pieces, handmade in limited numbers. When they&rsquo;re gone, they&rsquo;re gone.</p>
